{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it mandatory for taxi drivers to wear a mask when taking children to school",
        "additional_details": "Masks must be worn on public transport so why are private taxi drivers exempt from wearing one? I can understand if they are behind a screen but not when they are in a small van with six secondary age special needs children. This is an enclosed space and they are travelling together for up to 4 hours a day to and from school",
        "background": "I would like to see private taxi drivers have to wear a mask when transporting  children to school. The taxi driver is in close proximity to the children for hours in a small van and is not wearing a mask. I do not feel this is acceptable as the driver is mixing with passengers all day",
